        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 19 at 4:22PM CDT until May 19 at 4:45PM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Weir, or near
Pittsburg, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Pittsburg, Frontenac, Columbus, Girard, Arma, Cherokee, Weir,
Sherman, Scammon, Chicopee, Mccune, Mindenmines, Franklin, West
Mineral, Roseland, Beulah, Yale, Carona, Hallowell, and Sherwin.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for southeastern
Kansas...and southwestern Missouri.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
